Center: Center of Nuclear Physics Data, Russian Federal Nuclear Center (VNIIEF), Sarov, Russia
title: Excitation functions of the reactions Ag-109(p,n); Ag-109(d,2n); Ag-107(a,2n+pn) and yield of Cd-109.

x4freetext: Excitation functions of the reactions Ag-109(p,n);
Ag-109(d,2n); Ag-107(a,2n+pn) and yield of Cd-109.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Atomic Energy, Vol.22, p.386 (1967)

x4freetext: English translation
1.5-m cyclotron
Stack of foils and thick samples of natural Ag were
used.
Na(I)Tl crystal (40*50 mm) was used for
determination of Cd-109 activity.
Stacks of foils from natural silver were
irradiated on the deflected cyclotron beam. The energy
for protons was 22 MeV, for deuterons - 21.0 MeV, and
for alpha-particles it was 42 MeV. Accuracy of the beam
energy determination was approximately 0.5 MeV for
protons and deuterons, and approximately 1.0 MeV for
alpha-particles.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Error of cross section and yield
determination was due to the uncertainties in
measurements of Cd-109 activity, beam current
determination and projectile energy.
In Sub 001 ERR-ANALYS was changed,
"EC" in DECAY-DATA was deleted.
